1
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:11,800
<i>Are you with Manuel?
I need to talk to him.</i>

2
00:00:11,933 --> 00:00:14,233
<i>Sorry, girl. Do not disturb him.</i>

3
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:17,100
<i> He's with his real family.</i>

4
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:20,533
<i>We'll make lots of memories
you'll never forget.</i>

5
00:00:20,667 --> 00:00:22,900
<i>A bad element
just arrived.</i>

6
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:25,867
<i>- It's Hazel.
- Hazel's here?</i>

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,267
<i> What is that? What's going on?</i>

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:29,167
<i>Let's talk
like civilized people.</i>

9
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:30,500
<i> How dare you!</i>

10
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:33,433
<i>- Sit.
- Let's talk properly.</i>

11
00:00:39,033 --> 00:00:40,167
Hi!

12
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:41,567
Hi, Luke.

13
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:44,067
Hi, JB.

14
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:46,767
- Is there a problem?
- Oh, no.

15
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:47,633
None.

16
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:48,900
Here's the thing.

17
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:53,800
My boss and her best friend
had a fight.

18
00:00:53,933 --> 00:00:55,100
World War III.

19
00:00:55,233 --> 00:01:00,000
So we just let them talk it out
so they'll make up soon.

20
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:01,033
Everything okay?

21
00:01:01,167 --> 00:01:02,300
Oh, absolutely!

22
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:05,067
Everything's perfectly fine.
Yes.

23
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:07,100
I'll handle things here.

24
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:08,100
All right, Ma'am.

25
00:01:08,233 --> 00:01:09,100
- Dont worry.
- If you need anything,

26
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:10,067
just call the phone.

27
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:13,500
I might call you later tonight.

28
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:15,300
We're fine here. I've got this.

29
00:01:15,433 --> 00:01:16,633
- All right, Ma'am.
- Yes.

30
00:01:16,767 --> 00:01:18,100
No problem, JB.

31
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:20,267
Yeah.

32
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:23,967
- Stay right there!
- Right here!

33
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:25,100
What's going on?

34
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:27,133
- Serves you right!
- Ouch!

35
00:01:27,267 --> 00:01:28,667
Ouch!

36
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:30,133
Ouch!

37
00:01:30,267 --> 00:01:34,267
At last, we meet again,
Miss Martinez,

38
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:38,400
A.K.A. the right hand
of the queen of witches!

39
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:39,400
Go ahead!

40
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:41,033
Hurt me!

41
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,800
I'll scream "assault"!

42
00:01:42,933 --> 00:01:44,767
And I'll tell the staff

43
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:47,133
you're ganging up
on my friend and me!

44
00:01:47,267 --> 00:01:49,467
- Wow!
- Wow!

45
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:50,900
Hey, they're gone.

46
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:53,467
I chased them off with my charm.

47
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,600
And you're being so dramatic.

48
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:57,400
What do you mean
by "ganging up"?

49
00:01:57,533 --> 00:01:58,400
You saw them.

50
00:01:58,533 --> 00:02:01,533
It's just the two of
them talking over there.

51
00:02:01,667 --> 00:02:03,300
Oh, wait.

52
00:02:03,433 --> 00:02:06,300
You're scared for
your lord and master?

53
00:02:06,433 --> 00:02:11,233
So you're admitting that Felma
can handle that witch Hazel!

54
00:02:11,367 --> 00:02:12,833
Of course not!

55
00:02:12,967 --> 00:02:16,133
Then there you go!

56
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:18,000
You talk too much,
you know that?

57
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:18,933
Hold on!

58
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:20,933
What are you and Hazel
even doing here?

59
00:02:21,067 --> 00:02:24,500
How did you track down
Manuel and Felma?

60
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:27,800
- Yes, how?
- Because of you, obviously!

61
00:02:27,933 --> 00:02:34,533
When you video-called Hazel,
I saw the resort's name.

62
00:02:34,667 --> 00:02:37,300
It was your fault, Ma'am Paz.

63
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:39,900
Don't blame me.
Just go to Manuel and the kids.

64
00:02:40,033 --> 00:02:41,400
They might start
looking for us.

65
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:42,600
Go on, go on.

66
00:02:42,733 --> 00:02:44,800
I'm not leaving Miss Felma.

67
00:02:44,933 --> 00:02:46,500
She might need backup, okay?

68
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:48,033
Didang, go. Go over there.

69
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:50,267
If Manuel finds out
Hazel is here,

70
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,667
the whole family night
will be ruined.

71
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,033
Go! Go, go!

72
00:02:53,167 --> 00:02:55,733
And I'm not even done
I'm so annoyed at that woman!

73
00:02:55,867 --> 00:02:59,367
- I'll handle it. Go, go.
- Yes, go.

74
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:05,933
Wow, you're so good at it.

75
00:03:06,067 --> 00:03:07,867
Of course, Dad.
You may not know,

76
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,900
but I was a patrol leader
in Boy Scouts.

77
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:13,300
And we always won Best Campfire.

78
00:03:13,433 --> 00:03:14,600
Because of me.

79
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:18,233
You're good. So fast.

80
00:03:18,367 --> 00:03:21,000
I learned some techniques
from Uncle Noah...

81
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,467
You know,

82
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:31,000
I should really thank Noah.

83
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:35,700
Because he became your father
figure when I wasn't here.

84
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:39,200
Son, now that Noah's back,

85
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:43,600
maybe you can keep that bond
with him, okay?

86
00:03:43,733 --> 00:03:47,000
Treat him like your dad.

87
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:49,633
What are you
talking about, Dad?

88
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:53,933
We don't need another dad.
You're here now, Dad. Okay?

89
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:55,600
Jeff....

90
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:57,533
he treated you like his kids,

91
00:03:57,667 --> 00:04:00,867
It wouldn't be right to
just turn your back on him.

92
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,633
Dad, are you okay?

93
00:04:02,767 --> 00:04:06,167
Because you keep pushing
us toward Uncle Noah.

94
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:08,267
Dad, Uncle Noah...

95
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:11,433
we'll never forget him.
He's part of our lives.

96
00:04:11,567 --> 00:04:13,600
There won't be any other...

97
00:04:13,733 --> 00:04:14,833
uncle.

98
00:04:14,967 --> 00:04:16,167
Okay, Dad?

99
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:19,267
The only uncle in our lives
is Uncle Noah.

100
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,900
Uncle. Okay?

101
00:04:22,033 --> 00:04:23,833
Your fire's uneven.

102
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:25,033
- Oh, geez!
- Fix the wood.

103
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:27,400
Right. It's ruining
the bragging I made.

104
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:30,300
- See that?
- That's what I'm saying.

105
00:04:30,433 --> 00:04:32,033
Hold on.

106
00:04:32,167 --> 00:04:34,667
Wait. Where's the fan?

107
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,933
- There you go.
- The fire's out.

108
00:04:40,567 --> 00:04:42,167
Why are you here?

109
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:45,267
Because Manuel and I
have an agreement.

110
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,967
He's coming home to me.

111
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:48,333
You don't know that?

112
00:04:48,467 --> 00:04:49,600
I know.

113
00:04:49,733 --> 00:04:51,633
If that's the case,

114
00:04:51,767 --> 00:04:53,767
why are you all here having fun?

115
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:56,200
Are you doing this on purpose?

116
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:58,267
My child just died.

117
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:01,467
And you have the nerve
to celebrate?

118
00:05:02,367 --> 00:05:04,567
This isn't a celebration, Hazel.

119
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:05,967
Then what is it?

120
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:07,800
A farewell.

121
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,967
For almost two decades,

122
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:13,967
my kids doesn't have a father.

123
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:16,467
They grew up without Manuel.

124
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:20,567
They never had him
at gatherings.

125
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:22,533
All the special moments,

126
00:05:22,667 --> 00:05:24,367
the happy occasions...

127
00:05:25,633 --> 00:05:27,467
birthdays,

128
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,200
Christmas,

129
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:30,500
New Year.

130
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:31,900
Nothing.

131
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,067
Because he was with you.

132
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:36,233
So?

133
00:05:38,033 --> 00:05:39,700
It's my fault?

134
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:43,833
- Are you blaming me?
- I'm just explaining.

135
00:05:45,467 --> 00:05:47,867
So you'll understand

136
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,967
that this is their one
and only chance,

137
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,800
the last time,

138
00:05:53,933 --> 00:05:56,233
for my children to be happy
with their father.

139
00:05:56,467 --> 00:05:58,067
So what I want now,

140
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:01,867
before Manuel leaves
the kids again,

141
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:06,100
at least give them memories
they can carry with them.

142
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,067
So don't interfere.

143
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:13,000
Don't ruin it.

144
00:06:13,133 --> 00:06:15,800
Because after tonight,

145
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:17,200
he's all yours.

146
00:06:28,267 --> 00:06:30,667
Oh! Oh no,
this is burnt already.

147
00:06:34,867 --> 00:06:36,433
What is this, Andeng?

148
00:06:36,567 --> 00:06:38,933
You still don't know
how to grill?

149
00:06:39,067 --> 00:06:40,533
Go on, I'll do it.

150
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,767
No, let Didang do it.

151
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:44,133
- Didang, you do this.
- Let me, I'll take over.

152
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:46,700
I got this.

153
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:51,700
Remember when you were little?

154
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:56,133
Whenever I grilled,
you always wanted to help.

155
00:06:56,267 --> 00:06:57,767
But I never let you.

156
00:06:59,467 --> 00:07:02,033
Because I always
burned things.

157
00:07:03,967 --> 00:07:06,667
Sorry, Dad,
I didn't get to practice.

158
00:07:08,133 --> 00:07:11,967
I haven't grilled
barbecue since...

159
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:14,667
Since I disappeared.

160
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,900
Ah, wait, dear.

161
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:20,067
Don't tell me...

162
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,367
you still don't know
how to tie your shoelaces?

163
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,000
Oh...

164
00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:26,267
Ah...

165
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,700
- You still don't?
- Dad!

166
00:07:30,267 --> 00:07:32,200
I don't! Okay?

167
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:36,467
I never learned because
I stopped wearing rubber shoes

168
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:39,900
and anything with laces.

169
00:07:40,033 --> 00:07:42,633
Because I never learned
how to tie shoelaces,

170
00:07:42,767 --> 00:07:45,567
because you used to tie
my shoes for me.

171
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,000
Come on, Andeng.

172
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,033
You're all grown up, and you
still don't know how?

173
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:49,933
Oh...

174
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:51,433
- Big brother!
- Why?

175
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:52,633
What?

176
00:07:54,367 --> 00:07:56,567
I don't need to learn
anymore, right, Dad?

177
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,400
Because you're here now.

178
00:07:58,533 --> 00:08:00,067
- Wow!
- You'll do it again for me,

179
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,067
- right, Dad?
- Just when you got older,

180
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,500
but you still want
to be spoiled by Dad.

181
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:06,100
- So what?
- Oh.

182
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:09,900
Why else was I Dad's
little Andeng?

183
00:08:10,033 --> 00:08:12,567
Oh, you want to be
spoiled again?

184
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,333
Dad, you know what else
she can't do?

185
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:17,133
- What?
- Ride a bike.

186
00:08:17,267 --> 00:08:18,567
Yup!

187
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,000
And she never tried learning it

188
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:21,833
since you left for Saudi Arabia.

189
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:25,900
- Well...
- Now...

190
00:08:26,033 --> 00:08:26,967
ask Dad to teach you
how to ride a bike

191
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,167
Just kidding, Dad.

192
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,767
- Kidding!
- No, why?

193
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,333
Joel, hold this.

194
00:08:33,433 --> 00:08:35,200
When Dad can walk again,

195
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,567
he'll teach me to bike,
right, Dad?

196
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,033
I'll just wait
until you can walk.

197
00:08:38,167 --> 00:08:42,367
Andeng, dear, learn everything
you can learn now.

198
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,133
Don't rely on me.

199
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:47,800
So when we're apart,
you can manage.

200
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:50,167
Dad, didn't...

201
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:53,833
we promise each other
we wouldn't be apart again?

202
00:08:59,033 --> 00:08:59,633
Let me get a hug, too.

203
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:01,433
- Oh!
- Get off!

204
00:09:01,567 --> 00:09:04,000
We're taking a picture!

205
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,433
Picture, picture!

206
00:09:10,533 --> 00:09:12,567
Ah, Didang, where's Mom?

207
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:15,433
Oh, dear, she's calming down
Miss Paz

208
00:09:15,567 --> 00:09:17,167
and Sir Abel.

209
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:18,500
They had a little
lovers' quarrel.

210
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:20,400
They said we should start,

211
00:09:20,533 --> 00:09:21,833
and they'll catch up.

212
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,533
Oh, I brought something.

213
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,067
Do you hear anything?

214
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,033
Not really.

215
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:30,467
Press harder.

216
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,833
That hurts.

217
00:09:31,967 --> 00:09:33,200
It'll hurt only at the start.

218
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,867
Wait a sec...

219
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,700
You seem to be talking about
something else.

220
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:39,133
Huh?

221
00:09:39,267 --> 00:09:40,967
Huh?

222
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,433
You two had something going on

223
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:43,600
back in Saudi Arabia,
didn't you?

224
00:09:43,733 --> 00:09:46,300
-Hey!
-Oh! Look at those guilty faces!

225
00:09:46,433 --> 00:09:48,700
- Your Honor, guilty!
- What?

226
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:50,233
No way! Huh?

227
00:09:50,367 --> 00:09:53,933
I like foreigners, or at least
someone who looks like one.

228
00:09:54,067 --> 00:09:55,400
Abel? Not my type at all.

229
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:57,933
- Ew!
- Ew?

230
00:09:58,067 --> 00:10:00,833
Wow, the nerve, Alice!

231
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,967
Look, Abel, no offense.

232
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,167
Nothing personal.

233
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,433
I just have a taste.

234
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:09,000
So you're saying
I don't have taste?

235
00:10:09,133 --> 00:10:10,767
You do.

236
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:12,133
But...

237
00:10:15,133 --> 00:10:17,200
it's poor taste.

238
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:18,600
Wow!

239
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:20,633
Poor taste?
You think you're that pretty?

240
00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:22,533
Pretty, huh?

241
00:10:22,667 --> 00:10:24,300
- Hello, huh?
- So pretty.

242
00:10:24,433 --> 00:10:25,667
It's me.

243
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:26,967
- Wow, so pretty...
- It's obvious, right?

244
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,100
I look like an actress!

245
00:10:28,233 --> 00:10:29,767
- Don't I?
- A look like who?

246
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:32,100
Looking like them is different
from sounding like them!

247
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:33,967
I look like her!
And I'm just as gorgeous!

248
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:36,933
- No!
- Not really,

249
00:10:37,067 --> 00:10:38,100
- not really.
- Really?

250
00:10:38,233 --> 00:10:39,167
Look at my face!

251
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:40,367
How can you look like her?

252
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:42,633
After your nape is your feet!

253
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:46,733
You're so noisy!

254
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:48,900
We can't hear
what's going on inside!

255
00:10:49,033 --> 00:10:50,100
It's her fault.

256
00:10:52,167 --> 00:10:53,600
It's cramped!
Move over!

257
00:10:58,033 --> 00:10:59,367
Fine, Felma.

258
00:11:00,967 --> 00:11:02,100
Since you're desperate...

259
00:11:03,133 --> 00:11:04,567
I'll grant your wish.

260
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:08,500
I'll lend you this night.

261
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:13,967
But after this, you're never
allowed to go near Manuel again.

262
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:15,567
Especially you.

263
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:32,933
Hazel... why Manuel?

264
00:11:33,967 --> 00:11:36,233
Out of all the men
in Saudi Arabia....

265
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:41,333
from all sorts
of nationalities...

266
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:43,033
why him?

267
00:11:43,167 --> 00:11:47,300
When you knew he had
a family he left behind?

268
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:52,533
Did you even truly love him?

269
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:58,767
Because from what Manuel
told me, you didn't.

270
00:11:58,900 --> 00:11:59,767
So what is it, really?

271
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,800
What is this, an interrogation?

272
00:12:03,933 --> 00:12:05,333
Digging up the past?

273
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,733
Why?

274
00:12:07,867 --> 00:12:09,400
Are we close?

275
00:12:10,533 --> 00:12:13,133
I just don't understand.

276
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:18,767
Why do you keep chasing
after him until now?

277
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:21,267
Because he's my husband.

278
00:12:21,633 --> 00:12:23,833
Of course, I'll chase him.

279
00:12:23,967 --> 00:12:25,100
Of course, I'll take him back

280
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:27,533
from those trying
to steal him from me.

281
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:30,967
Especially now
that I'm all alone.

282
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:33,300
Jessica's gone.

283
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:35,500
Unlike you...

284
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:38,200
You still have your kids.

285
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:39,967
And because I'll help Coleen...

286
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,800
Manuel will come home to me.

287
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,833
He's all I have left.

288
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:49,933
He's the only one
I can hold on to.

289
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,433
Even if he doesn't love you?

290
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:56,033
He will love me.

291
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:00,267
He'll love me
once we're together again.

292
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:05,067
Once I show him
how much I love him...

293
00:13:06,633 --> 00:13:08,667
how I care for him.

294
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,233
I'll serve him...

295
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:16,200
until he sees
I'm worthy of his love.

296
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:20,600
Don't count on it.

297
00:13:23,267 --> 00:13:25,233
He loves me.

298
00:13:26,933 --> 00:13:28,333
Only me.

299
00:13:38,367 --> 00:13:40,200
We're so happy right now, Dad.

300
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:43,267
I wish we could stay
like this forever.

301
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,800
You will, dear.

302
00:13:45,933 --> 00:13:48,333
You'll always be happy.

303
00:13:48,467 --> 00:13:49,433
Dad...

304
00:13:49,567 --> 00:13:50,767
us.

305
00:13:59,733 --> 00:14:00,900
What is it, sweetheart??

306
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,667
I just remembered Jessica, Dad.

307
00:14:06,367 --> 00:14:08,633
I wish she were here with us.

308
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:13,467
I'm sorry, because of me, Dad...

309
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,800
Hey, dear.

310
00:14:15,933 --> 00:14:19,433
Didn't we agree we'd stay happy?

311
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,800
And how many times
do I have to tell you

312
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:24,700
that it wasn't your fault?

313
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:29,600
I just can't help
blaming myself, Dad.

314
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,233
I was the first one
who got close to Jessica.

315
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:35,500
But I was also the one
who got insecure.

316
00:14:36,967 --> 00:14:39,733
I should've been
a better sister.

317
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:44,033
I shouldn't have been jealous.

318
00:14:44,167 --> 00:14:46,300
I was immature.

319
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:47,633
Selfish.

320
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:50,267
Sweetie, maybe try to...

321
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:53,900
think of all the happy memories
you shared with Jessica.

322
00:14:54,033 --> 00:14:55,533
Because I'm sure,

323
00:14:55,667 --> 00:14:57,700
that's what she's carrying
with her in heaven.

324
00:14:59,367 --> 00:15:01,600
Can you do that, dear? For me?

325
00:15:04,367 --> 00:15:05,667
Okay, Dad.

326
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,433
Promise?

327
00:15:08,467 --> 00:15:09,733
And sweetheart,

328
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:13,300
take care of yourself, okay?

329
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:15,933
Don't be stubborn.

330
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:18,567
Love your siblings.

331
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:20,400
And especially your mom.

332
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:23,800
Yes, Dad.

333
00:15:36,067 --> 00:15:37,767
So what now?

334
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:38,867
Feel like you've won?

335
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:43,100
Fine.
You're the one Manuel loves.

336
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:45,700
But I'll be the one
he goes home to.

337
00:15:47,067 --> 00:15:49,167
I'll be the one
he lives with every day.

338
00:15:50,533 --> 00:15:53,633
The one beside him every night.

339
00:15:53,767 --> 00:15:55,333
And above all...

340
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:56,967
I am still the one...

341
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:59,600
and only Mrs. Cruz.

342
00:16:02,467 --> 00:16:05,067
No one's stealing your title.

343
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,267
But remember this.

344
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:10,467
Your name may be on the...

345
00:16:10,633 --> 00:16:12,800
paper as his wife...

346
00:16:15,133 --> 00:16:16,800
but in Manuel's heart,

347
00:16:18,767 --> 00:16:21,867
it's my name carved there.

348
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:27,233
And you can never...

349
00:16:27,367 --> 00:16:29,800
erase that, Hazel.

350
00:16:54,233 --> 00:16:55,500
Sis.

351
00:16:55,633 --> 00:16:56,967
Friend.

352
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:10,333
But Sis, what happened
back there?

353
00:17:10,467 --> 00:17:11,167
Oh, never mind.

354
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,767
Let's not waste time.

355
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:16,333
Let's make the most of tonight,
we have to be happy.

356
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:18,567
And remember
our agreement, okay?

357
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:20,233
No one tells Manuel

358
00:17:20,367 --> 00:17:23,133
or the kids that Hazel is here.

359
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,467
- Come on.
- But, Sis...

360
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:28,100
No more, come on.

361
00:17:30,967 --> 00:17:32,567
- Ah, Ma'am Felma!
- Mom!

362
00:17:32,700 --> 00:17:35,500
- Mom!
- Ma'am Felma, how was

363
00:17:35,633 --> 00:17:38,033
- their lovers' quarrel?
- We're okay now.

364
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:39,600
Thank you, Sis.

365
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:44,633
Oh!

366
00:17:44,767 --> 00:17:47,600
Come on! If everything's fine,
then let's party!

367
00:17:49,067 --> 00:17:50,433
But let's eat first.

368
00:17:50,567 --> 00:17:51,833
Where's the food?

369
00:17:51,967 --> 00:17:53,367
- Ah...
- You, Didang!

370
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:54,733
- You first! Ma'am Paz!
- You do it, Mom.

371
00:17:54,867 --> 00:17:55,867
Hurry!

372
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:00,067
Huh? Who?

373
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,867
There, it's going there.

374
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,500
They already started eating.

375
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:05,400
Ready to eat?

376
00:18:05,533 --> 00:18:07,567
- Come on.
- There you go.

377
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:08,800
- Let's go, Dad!
- Big sister, oh.

378
00:18:08,933 --> 00:18:10,933
- Oh.
- There!

379
00:18:11,067 --> 00:18:13,733
What do you want?
There's more here.

380
00:18:13,867 --> 00:18:16,167
- Here you go
- What do you want, Dad?

381
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:17,633
- Here's more!
- Bro.

382
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:19,333
Barbecue for Dad.

383
00:18:19,467 --> 00:18:21,067
- It's still on the grill.
- Wow, here's some pork belly.

384
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:22,333
- Yes, it burned.
- No.

385
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:23,800
Right, let's put a new batch.

386
00:18:23,933 --> 00:18:26,000
That's not the one I cooked.

387
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:28,600
I thought it was
really you singing.

388
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:41,167
Wait! On my phone, too! All four
of us.

389
00:18:45,367 --> 00:18:47,200
Wait, groupfie!

390
00:18:48,167 --> 00:18:49,433
Selfie with everyone!

391
00:18:51,567 --> 00:18:56,200
One, two, three!

392
00:19:01,367 --> 00:19:02,267
Jeffrey!

393
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:04,133
Go, Jeffrey! Go, Jeffrey!

394
00:19:04,267 --> 00:19:05,933
- Go, Jeffrey!
- Big sister Andeng!

395
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:07,767
Beat him!

396
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:12,433
Go, Joel!

397
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:20,833
Picture taking?
Really?

398
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:36,933
Take care of them for me, okay?

399
00:19:40,033 --> 00:19:42,000
And take care of yourself, too.

400
00:19:44,033 --> 00:19:46,800
Don't forget
to take your medicine.

401
00:19:50,667 --> 00:19:53,833
But please, your therapy
sessions with Doctor Tamayo...

402
00:19:55,067 --> 00:19:56,367
just continue it.

403
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:03,967
Felma, get your frequent
headaches checked, okay?

404
00:20:04,133 --> 00:20:05,633
No.

405
00:20:09,167 --> 00:20:11,033
It goes away quickly anyway.

406
00:20:11,733 --> 00:20:13,133
It's just stress.

407
00:20:13,267 --> 00:20:17,000
Oh, stubborn as always.

408
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:19,067
Just promise me
you'll have it checked.

409
00:20:20,967 --> 00:20:24,733
Fine, I will.

410
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:14,033
<i> Don't get your hopes up.</i>

411
00:21:14,767 --> 00:21:17,100
<i> He loves me.</i>

412
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:18,600
<i> Only me.</i>

413
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:22,300
<i> No one's taking your title.</i>

414
00:21:22,433 --> 00:21:24,267
<i> But remember this.</i>

415
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:28,967
<i>Your name may be
on the papers as his wife,</i>

416
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:34,400
<i>but in Manuel's heart,
it's my name engraved there.</i>

417
00:21:56,333 --> 00:21:57,667
- Oh, Didang
- Ma'am.

418
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:01,167
Did you finish arranging
the souvenirs for the FMP staff?

419
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:02,367
Yes, Ma'am.

420
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:03,967
- They're all ready.
- Where are the kids?

421
00:22:04,100 --> 00:22:05,633
Why aren't they in the room?

422
00:22:05,767 --> 00:22:07,033
They were tired from the trip.

423
00:22:07,167 --> 00:22:08,767
- Huh?
- There they are.

424
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,367
Andrea!

425
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:04,567
Don't tell your siblings.

426
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:06,233
Fine, I won't leave anymore,
I'll stay here.

427
00:23:06,367 --> 00:23:07,600
I won't go back to Hazel.

428
00:23:07,733 --> 00:23:09,067
But we have to prepare ourselves

429
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:10,067
that Coleen might go to jail.

430
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,767
Good thing you're here already.

431
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:13,333
Welcome to our new home.

432
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:17,300
Lord, I hope the decision Manuel
and I made was right.

433
00:23:17,433 --> 00:23:19,333
Please watch over him.

434
00:23:19,467 --> 00:23:20,433
Good morning!

435
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:22,200
I'm here, Hazel.

436
00:23:22,333 --> 00:23:23,600
I kept my end of the deal.

437
00:23:23,733 --> 00:23:25,467
When will Timo
take back his statement?
